                                                       &lt;div class="synopsis-wrapper mt-8" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;"&gt;                                     &lt;div class="flex min-w-0 gap-x-6 items-start"&gt;                                         &lt;div class="mt-1"&gt;&lt;i class="fa-light fa-square-info text-center"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;                                         &lt;/div&gt;                                         &lt;div class="min-w-0 flex-auto"&gt;                                             &lt;p                                                 class="uppercase font-bold text-xs tracking-widest text-subheader font-serif"&gt;                                                 Synopsis                                             &lt;/p&gt;                                             &lt;div class="prose prose-darklight max-w-2xl"&gt;                                                 &lt;p&gt;On the run from the Time Lords and in serious need of help, the Doctor heads for 17th-century Russia in search of the legendary witch of Slavic folklore… Baba Yaga. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;But while trying to gain assistance from this powerful entity, the Doctor finds herself embroiled in events from the most famous of Baba Yaga's tales when the tries to help a beautiful young woman called Vasilisa retrieve a burning ember to save her family from the bitter Russian winter. What is real? What is fantasy? And will the Doctor be able to tell the difference in time?&lt;/p&gt;                                             &lt;/div&gt;                                         &lt;/div&gt;                                     &lt;/div&gt;                                 &lt;/div&gt;                                                                &lt;/div&gt;                         &lt;/div&gt;                          &lt;div class="mt-8 lg:mt-0"&gt;                               &lt;div class="lg:sticky lg:top-0 lg:pt-10 lg:-mt-10 w-64 lg:w-44 mx-auto lg:mx-0"&gt;               